[49m[38;5;9m- 100     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Feature Engineering and Aggregation.** Raw arrival records get aggregated to the hourly grid. Calendar features (hour of day, day of week, week of year, holiday markers) get added. External features (weather variables, flu index, event flags) get joined on. Lagged values (last hour's count, same hour yesterday, same hour last week) get computed. The output is a single tabular dataset where one row equals one (date, hour) pair with the count target and all features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Feature Engineering and Aggregation.** Raw arrival records get aggregated to the hourly grid. Calendar features (hour of day, day of week, week of year, holiday markers) get added. External features (weather variables, flu index, event flags) get joined on. Lagged values (last hour's count, same hour yesterday, same hour last week) get computed. The output is a single tabular dataset where one row equals one (date, hour) pair with the count target and all features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Late-Record Handling and Reconciliation.** ADT messages do not always arrive in order. A registration that happened at 14:32 might land in the stream at 14:45 because of EHR queue delays. Without explicit handling, lag features are systematically biased near the trailing edge. The pipeline enforces an event-time watermark on hourly aggregation with a configurable lateness tolerance (15 minutes by default). Records arriving after the watermark still get counted: a scheduled reconciliation pass runs every 4 to 6 hours, re-aggregates the prior 24 hours of arrivals from the source-of-truth stream, and writes delta records with a `revision` attribute when counts differ from the original aggregation. Inference reads only watermarked (finalized) hours: if the current hour is H, lag_1h draws from H-1, which is past its watermark and stable. When reconciled deltas exceed a configurable threshold, a backfill step re-generates the affected forecasts. CloudWatch metrics on `late_records_per_hour` and `reconciliation_delta_distribution` make the late-record rate visible to operations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Diversion-Log Integration and ESI Reconciliation.** Two additional reconciliation primitives share the same shape as the late-record pass. The diversion log (manually entered by the charge nurse or inferred from EMS routing data) joins into the feature table as a per-hour boolean indicator; training either excludes diversion-affected hours or includes them with the indicator as a feature so the model learns the suppression effect. The ESI-reconciliation second pass sweeps the prior 24 hours, finds placeholder `esi_unknown` values that have since received triage assignments, queries the EHR for triage updates, and writes corrections with a `revision` attribute. All three reconciliation passes (late-record, diversion-log, ESI) can be consolidated into a single reusable reconciliation primitive parameterized by data source and correction logic.
